name: Taman Sari Buwana
address: Banjar Beng UtaraTunjuk, G4CX+WMJ, Desa Tunjuk, Kecamatan Tabanan, Tunjuk, Kec. Tabanan, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82181, Indonesia
review 1: Really nice tour with lovely people.
review 2: A MUST go to in Bali. Such an incredible experience. Truly authentic and unlike other tourist spots, you get to actually interact with locals and learn from them traditional Balinese life and culture. The staff was very nice and the food was delicious!
review 3:
Awesome to see the real Bali village life. Our tour included visiting a school and a typical Balinese house, doing handicrafts with palm leaves, preparing rice cookies, planting rice, learning about the different trees, climbing a coconut tree, eating fresh coconut and having a delicious Balinese meal at the end.
Highly recommend!
review 4: The local villagers who helped us were all very friendly and helpful. And it's a great way to learn about Balinese traditional life and farming.
review 5: Place for find traditional Balinese Farming activity, very natural and enjoyable
